<FlowDocument PagePadding="5,0,5,0" AllowDrop="True" xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"><Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="16">Heat Map</Paragraph>
<Paragraph FontFamily="Calibri" FontSize="14">The following list includes the features illustrated for the <Run FontWeight="Bold" xml:space="preserve">Heat Map control</Run> (HMC).</Paragraph>
<Paragraph FontFamily="Calibri" FontSize="14"><Bold>Flat List Demo</Bold>-Demonstrates how flat list items are bound to a HMC</Paragraph>
<Paragraph FontFamily="Calibri" FontSize="14"><Bold>Hierarchical List Demo</Bold>-Demonstrates a hierarchical data model</Paragraph>
<Paragraph FontFamily="Calibri" FontSize="14"><Bold>LINQ Bound Demo</Bold>-Demonstrates how to bind data from a LINQ data source to a HMC</Paragraph>
<Paragraph FontFamily="Calibri" FontSize="14"><Run FontWeight="Bold">XML Binding Demo</Run>-Demonstrates how XML data can be bound to a Heat Map control</Paragraph>
<Paragraph FontFamily="Calibri" FontSize="14"><Bold>Collection View Source Heat Map Demo</Bold>-Demonstrates how to create a view of a data collection and bind it to a HMC</Paragraph>
<Paragraph FontFamily="Calibri" FontSize="14" xml:space="preserve"><Bold>Manual Items Demo</Bold>-Illustrates how to add items directly to a HMC</Paragraph>

